Did you know? The depiction of some items in the Assassin's Creed Mirage codex come directly from real museums!

As part of the 'Artifacts in Play' exhibition, visitors to Hawaiis Shangri La Museum of Islamic Art, Culture & Design can now see two such artifacts up close, along with insights into how real-world objects make their way into Assassins Creed.
This marks not only another exciting historical collaboration but also Ubisofts first-ever museum partnership in the U.S. A huge congratulations to everyone behind the scenes for bringing this to life
